A few days ago, I was waiting for a friend at a convenience store in my apartment. An elderly man walked in and suddenly said,
&ldquo;Where is building 109?&rdquo;
At first, I had to repeat myself a few times due to his inaccurate pronunciation. I soon realized that he was referring to building 109 in the apartment, so I turned on the map app and showed him the location. But after a while, he remained silent and asked again, &ldquo;Where is building 109?
